      "type": "term",
      "surface": {
        "jp": "無方式主義",
        "zh": "无方式主义",
        "en": "No-Formality Doctrine"
      },
      "definition": {
        "jp": "著作権のように、申請しなくても権利が発生すること。無方式主義を認めることで、申請に関する膨大な手間と労力を未然に防いでいる。",
        "zh": "指像著作权一样，无需申请即可产生权利。通过承认无方式主义，事先避免了与申请相关的大量繁琐与劳力消耗。",
        "en": "Like copyright, rights arise without any application. By adopting the no-formality doctrine, the enormous time and effort associated with applications are avoided in advance."
      },
      "kana_helper": null
    },
    {
      "id": "itpassport_r6::term::p071::3",
      "anchor": {
        "page": 71,
        "block_id": "page_071_block_3",
        "section_path": []
      },
      "type": "term",
      "surface": {
        "jp": "方式主義",
        "zh": "方式主义",
        "en": "Formality Doctrine"
      },
      "definition": {
        "jp": "権利を保護してもらうために申請が必要となること。",
        "zh": "指为了获得权利保护必须进行申请。",
        "en": "Requires an application in order for the rights to be protected."
      },
      "kana_helper": null
    },
    {
      "id": "itpassport_r6::term::p071::4",
      "anchor": {
        "page": 71,
        "block_id": "page_071_block_4",
        "section_path": []
      },
      "type": "term",
      "surface": {
        "jp": "著作権",
        "zh": "著作权",
        "en": "Copyright"
      },
      "definition": {
        "jp": "著作物を創作した時点で自動的に発生する権利（役所などへの申請は不要）。",
        "zh": "在创作作品时自动产生的权利（无需向政府机构等提出申请）。",
        "en": "A right that arises automatically at the moment a work is created (no application to government offices, etc. is required)."
      },
      "kana_helper": null
    }
